post_text:
SCC Volleyball Tournament Information for September 12:
Calhoun County is currently classified as a COVID "hot spot". Because of this, our school in conjunction with Calhoun County public health, have decided to implement the attached precautions for this weekend's JV volleyball tournament. Please get this information to your fans, JV volleyball players, and coaches immediately so that they can come prepared.

These precautions are only for the JV tournament in Lake City because of the smaller gym and the limited potential for social distancing. If your varsity team is playing in Rockwell City, masks are strongly encouraged but not required. The middle school has a much greater seating capacity and the opportunity to social distance is much greater.
More information at this link:https://bit.ly/2Rl3nCE

post_text:
Little Raptor Daycare is looking for a Director. Duties include but not limited to:
• Is responsible for overall functions of the center, supervising staff, and administering programs.
• Shall ensure services are provided for the children within the framework of the licensing requirements and the center’s statement of purpose and objectives.
• Has overall responsibility for carrying out the program and ensuring the safety and protection of the children.
• Must be 21 or older.
• Must have worked full time in a child care or daycare setting.
Applications available on our website under the employment tab. Questions can be directed to Superintendent Jon Wiebers - jwiebers@rvraptors.org or call 712-368-4353 ext 305.

post_text: On Thursday, May 21, 2020, the Iowa Department of Education stated that Iowa schools could not have Prom in June. This guidance was also reconfirmed by the Iowa Department of Education on the afternoon of Tuesday, May 26. While this news deeply saddens us, we must follow the guidance given to us from our governor and also from the Department of Education. I'm sorry to announce that Ridge View High School 2020 Prom is now cancelled.

Rogelio Sierra is with Dan Droegmiller and Kris Droegmiller in Holstein, Iowa.
May 20 at 9:15 AM · Holstein, IA ·

A little late but I want to give a big shout out and would like others to join me in congratulating PVT Jaden Droegmiller who will be headed to basic training next week! Jaden enlisted with us a while back as 15T (Blackhawk Helicopter Repairer) and it’s been a pleasure watching this Future Soldier grow. He is part of the 2020 graduating class from Ridge View High School. Can’t wait to see him progress even more and run into him further down the road in his Army Career!
text:
Congratulations Jaden!! Best of luck!
